      "content": "<|channel|>Thought\n<|channel|>I see your point, and I appreciate your attention to detail. The RFI for the utility line adjustment was indeed approved, but it was a minor issue that didn't require a full change order. The RFI number is RFI-1023, and the structural engineer, Dr. Smith, gave his nod on March 15th. The change was within the acceptable range, and it was documented in the project log. The utility line was a post-construction addition, and the foundation was poured with the understanding that minor adjustments could be made. The 2-inch shift is a small concession for the sake of practicality.",
